Guide to the Raymond Germann Photograph Collection
                    <lb/>1978-2016
                    <lb/>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Marybeth Kavanagh

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2017-04-21T16:19-0400</date>

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Raymond Germann Photograph Collection consists of over 300 archival inkjet photographs of New York City street scenes taken between 1978-2016. Four are color prints, the remainder are black and white prints.

p.value: Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to 20 exposures of stable, unbound material per day. Researchers may not accrue unused copy amounts from previous days.
This collection should be cited as: Raymond Germann Photograph Collection, PR 311, Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections, The New-York Historical Society.
This collection was a gift from the photographer, 2013, 2014, 2015 & 2016.
Note: the prints are numbered; There is NO print # 177, and NO prints #340-360.
